{{Infobox company | name = Bowers Group | logo = | type = | foundation = 1915 | location = [[Bradford]], [[West Yorkshire]], England | key_people = Roger Bowers | industry = [[Electronic test equipment|Test equipment]], [[Measuring instrument]]s | revenue = | products = [[Micrometer]]s | homepage = [http://www.bowersgroup.co.uk/ bowersgroup.co.uk] }}
'''Bowers Group''' founded in 1915 manufacture [[Electronic test equipment|Test equipment]] and [[Measuring instrument]]s. The group includes Baty International, Bowers Export, Bowers UK, Moore & Wright and CV Instruments.<ref name=hist />
==History== Originally known as 'Bowers Precision Engineers', established as a toolmaker in Bradford in 1915. In 1994 it developed a 3-point internal bore micrometer. In 1979 'Bowers Internal Gauge Company Limited' was found by Roger Bowers. The company moved to Bradford, West Yorkshire in 1989. In 2000, Bowers Metrological Group was founded.<ref name=hist /> In 2009, Bowers assisted the Nuclear Advanced Manufacturing Research Centre accurately measure internal [[screw thread]]s.<ref name=eng /> Baty International was acquired in 2010.<ref name=hist />
==References== {{reflist|20em|refs= <ref name=eng>{{cite web|title=Case study: Nuclear AMRC finds solution for internal thread measurement|url=http://source.theengineer.co.uk/measurement-quality-control-and-test/metrology-systems/hand-tools-for-gauging/case-study-nuclear-amrc-finds-solution-for-internal-thread-measurement/2019467.article|publisher=The Engineer|accessdate=20 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522223123/http://source.theengineer.co.uk/measurement-quality-control-and-test/metrology-systems/hand-tools-for-gauging/case-study-nuclear-amrc-finds-solution-for-internal-thread-measurement/2019467.article|archivedate=22 May 2015|df=}}</ref> <ref name=hist>{{cite web|title=A History of Bowers.|url=http://www.bowersgroup.co.uk/about/history/en/|publisher=Bowers Group|accessdate=20 April 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424050957/http://www.bowersgroup.co.uk/about/history/en/|archivedate=24 April 2015|df=}}</ref> }}
