{{Underlinked|date=February 2015}}
'''MOS (Magnetic Organization System)''' is an American brand of organizational tools that use [[magnetism]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MOS Magnetic Cable Organizer Magnetizes Your Cords and Holds Them Anywhere|url=http://lifehacker.com/5985366/mos-magnetic-cable-organizer-magnetizes-your-cords-and-holds-them-anywhere}}</ref> to manage cables and other magnetic items. The brand was formed through [[crowdfunding]] on [[Kickstarter]] in August 2012. MOS has launched every subsequent product through the Kickstarter platform since. In January 2014 MOS released Spring,<ref>{{cite web|title=Your Phone Will Break Before These Fortified Charging Cables Do|url=https://gizmodo.com/your-phone-will-break-before-these-fortified-charging-c-1580205077}}</ref> a line of phone and audio cables, as well as a miniaturized version of the original Magnetic Organization System called MOS Menos. Later in June 2014 MOS started another Kickstarter campaign for the Reach project<ref>{{cite web|title=MOS Reach offers power solution|url=http://www.macrumors.com/2014/06/26/mos-reach-power-solution/}}</ref> which made its goal of $50,000 in the first day of the Kickstarter campaign. The Reach campaign was funded at 284 percent of the initial goal on July 26, 2014. MOS is a brand of Sewell Development Corp.
