A '''mediastinoscope''' is a thin, tube-like instrument used to examine the tissues and [[lymph nodes]] in the area between the [[lungs]] ([[mediastinum]]) in a procedure known as [[mediastinoscopy]]. These tissues include the [[heart]] and its large [[blood vessels]], [[Vertebrate trachea|trachea]], [[esophagus]], and [[bronchi]]. The mediastinoscope has a light and a lens for viewing and may also have a tool to remove tissue. It is inserted into the [[chest]] through a cut above the [[Human breastbone|breastbone]].

